learning Python

1.For loop
for ... in ... :
  ...
[else :]
  ...
         
2.List comprehension
[expr for ... in ...]
[expr for ... in ... if cond_expr]

e.g: calculate the length of the maximum line of one file. 
return max([len(x.strip()) for x in open('/etc/motd')])

3.Generator expression
(expr for ... in ...)
(expr for ... in ... if cond_expr)

4.With statement
with context_expr [as var]:
  ...
  
5.range/xrange
range(end)
range(start, end)
range(start, end, step)

6.function decorator
@deco
def func():
  pass

is equivalent to: func = deco(func)

7.Generator
def generator()
  yield 1
  yield 2
  pass
  
8.ways to define static function and class function
@staticmethod
def f():
  pass

@classmethod
def f(cls):
  pass

9.regexp module
import re
re.compile, re.match, re.search

10.Iterator
Objects with next() method.
